Git & GitHub Fundamentals

Today's Focus: Version Control, Git Commands, GitHub Workflow
What I Learned: Tracking code changes and collaboration. Learned:

git init – initialize repository

git add – stage changes

git commit – save changes

git push – upload to GitHub

git pull – download from GitHub

Branches and merging

Pull requests

Practice Example: Daily Workflow

# Start new feature
git checkout -b feature/login-page

# Make changes and commit
git add .
git commit -m "Add login form with validation"

# Push to GitHub
git push origin feature/login-page

# Create pull request on GitHub website
Practice Questions:

Initialize repo for your portfolio website

Create and merge feature branch

Resolve merge conflict

Contribute to open source via fork and PR


